result.execSummary:
The defendant Cody W. Dykstra was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Strangulation and Suffocation [Modifiers: Domestic Abuse], a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 940.235(1).
  • Disorderly Conduct [Modifiers: Domestic Abuse], a class B misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 947.01(1).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt:
02:05 PM in Room 301. Defendant Cody W. Dykstra in court with attorney John Zich.  Defendant Cody W. Dykstra in custody at Langlade County Jail.  Kelly L Hays appeared for the State of Wisconsin. State recites agreement. Def. to plead to Ct. 1 and Ct. 4. Joint recommendation: Ct. 1 - withheld sentence, 3 years probation, court costs, AODA and treatment, abs. sobriety, domestic violence assessment and followthru, no presence in establishments with Class B liquor license, no contact with victim except with her and agent approval.   Ct. 4 - 60 days jail, court costs. Cts. 2 and 3 to be DRI. Attny Zich in agreement. Def. agrees with terms. Waiver of P.H. already held. Plea questionnaire reviewed.  Def. pleads to Ct. 1 - Strangulation and suffocation, domestic abuse, guilty; Ct. 4 - Disorderly conduct, domestic abuse, guilty. The Court will grant State's motion to DRI Cts. 2 and 3. Constitutional rights, elements and possible penalties reviewed.  Attny Zich is satisfied. Court finds that Def. understands and that pleas are freely and voluntarily given. The Court finds there is a factual basis, accepts pleas and finds Def. guilty of Ct. 1 and Ct. 4, both in domestic abuse setting. Sentencing remarks by State. State is in compliance with victim rights. No restitution requested. Sentencing remarks by Attny Zich. Def. has nothing to say. Remarks by the Court. 
The Court will abide by agreement, orders  Ct. 1 - withheld sentence, 3 years probation, court costs only including DNA surcharge, DNA sample, AODA assessment and followthru, maintain absolute sobriety, no presence in establishments with Class B liquor license, complete a domestic violence assessment and followthru with any recommendations,  no contact with victim unless victim and supervising agent consents, counseling as deemed beneficial by agent.   Ct. 4 - 60 days jail, Huber, court costs only. Firearm/voting rights. If probation is revoked or discharged with outstanding financial obligations, a civil judgment shall be entered, without further order of the court, against the defendant in favor of restitution victims and/or governmental entities for the balance due.  All available enforcement actions will be used to collect the debt. Post conviction rights. 
Credit: 40 days.
